On Mon, Jun 28, 2010 at 11:29 AM, David Kelly <volknstein(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> I have a type 1 motor and I usually drain the oil by removing the center bolt
> first, then I remove the round plate.

Right. We are dealing with a Type 4 motor here. The round plate
retaining stud and boss it is mounted into is a weak point on the Type
4. Spec is only 9 foot pounds, and the boss is easily broken,
rendering the engine case useless.

